text:
I understand that mouse events are captured by the JSVGCanvas.

I have added a mouse listener to the canvas which finds the graphics node 
corresponding to the mouse hit on the canvas.

JSVGCanvas svgCanvas;
public void mouseClicked(MouseEvent e) {
  Point2D.Double pt = new Point2D.Double(e.getX(), e.getY());
  GraphicsNode gNode = svgCanvas.getGraphicsNode().nodeHitAt(pt);
}

My question is how map this graphics node back to the corresponding SVGElement 
in the SVGDocument as I cannot add event listeners to individual SVG elements 
as events are trapped by the JSVGCanvas.

Thanks
Belinda.
